The paper deals with computational geometry and algorithms for computing Fr\'echet distance between curves, which are typical topics in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and data structures, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and optimization suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.SI (Systems and Control).
